Look at the article "Decoding a VCR controller Code" by K. Shirriff,
C. Welch and A. Kinsman in the July 1992 issue of Cryptologia (v. XVI
no. 3).  The decode the 1 to 6 digit codes, but hadn't yet succeeded
with the 7 and 8 digit codes.  Apparently, the VCR plus people wanted
to quash competition by keeping the coding method a trade secret.
Well, I guess that didn't work.
